<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph>Visibility property used to set the visibility property of the interactive cursor.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Using the Cursor property we can set any style of the cursor to the interactive cursor.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Using the HorizontalStroke and VerticalStroke we can set the stroke of the horizontal and vertical lines.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>IsBindWithSegment property allows the user to move along the chart segment. If IsBindWithSegment is false, user can move the cursor over the chart area.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>BindWithMouseMoveOnSegment property allows the user to move freely on the segments</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>StrokeThickness property used to set the stroke thickness of the cursor lines.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>


<List Margin="25,0,0,0">

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Cursor Visibility  "</Bold> set the visibility for the Cursor</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Cursor"</Bold> will help in selecting the cursor of the Interactive Cursor.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Horizontal Cursor Stroke"</Bold> will help in selecting the color for the Horizontal cursor.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Vertical Cursor Stroke"</Bold> will let you to select the color for the Vertical cursor.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Check box <Bold>"IsBind With Segment"</Bold> allows you to drag the cursor over the Segment of the Chart series.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Check box <Bold>"Bind With MouseMove On Segment"</Bold> allows you to drag the cursor over the selected series.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Text box <Bold>"Stroke Thickness"</Bold> allows you to set the thickness for the cursor stroke.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
</List>
